<br>
Asking for a longer duration is asking for a more poewrfull spell. So it will probably not happen.<br>
<br>
But how about if we ask for a SHORTER duration on the spell? =). If the DS lasts 2 minutes, has a short caasting time, and has 1/3 the mana cost, we can simply cast it on every pull. That way we don't have to speculate wether the MT still has it or not, because we can assume that he is not.<br>
<br>
It would maintain the mana/damage ratios of the DS. It would make us cast it more often, both in the sence that we would always use it, and in the sence that when we use it we need to cast it more frequently.<br>
<br>
